Same problem happenened with an RDP connection to a Windows 10 machine (Fedora 30). With Reminna the connection works without any problems. 

gnome-boxes-3.32.0.2-2.fc30.1.x86_64

@felipeborges I think you can remove the label as it is confirmed that other clients seem to work fine

Here's some slightly-more idiomatic GAsyncResult code, and it also fails, as above.

```
#include <gio/gio.h>

static void
on_ready_get_result (GObject *source,
                     GAsyncResult *result,
                     gpointer user_data)
{
  GError **error = user_data;
  GSocketConnection *connection;

  connection = g_socket_client_connect_to_host_finish (G_SOCKET_CLIENT (source), result, error);
  g_assert (connection == NULL);
}

int
main (void)
{
  g_autoptr(GSocketClient) client = g_socket_client_new ();
  g_autoptr(GError) error = NULL;

  g_socket_client_connect_to_host_async (client, "localhost", 1234, NULL,
                                         on_ready_get_result, &error);

  while (error == NULL)
    g_main_context_iteration (NULL, TRUE);

  g_printerr ("error: %s\n", error->message);

  return 0;
}
```

